The sensitivity of CZCH-4 toward detecting TC concentration was further analyzed under optimized conditions. The fluorescence response of CZCH-4 toward TC was found to be dependent on TC concentration, as evidenced by the observed fluorescence quenching in Fig. 6
                        a. The linear correlation equation was obtained for analysis on AQY and C0 in the range of 1–300 mg/L. The regression equation was expressed as follows: AQY =  − 0.0013 × C0 + 5.0296, where C0 denoted TC concentration. In addition, the fluorescence intensity of the CZCH-4 decreased gradually with increasing TC concentration (Fig. 6b). The linear regression equation was expressed as follows: I0/I − 1 =  − 0.0703 × C0 + 0.0004. The LOD was determined to be 0.09 μg/L according to 3σ/k [61], where σ denoted the standard deviation and k denoted the slope of the calibration plot. The detection performance of CZCH-4 was compared to other reported fluorescent probes (Table 2
                        ). The results showed that the CZCH-4 was superior to the LOD and linear range.
